      "block_id": "ca_intro",
      "always_include": true,
      "text": "## 7. Client Acceptance Framework\n\n### 7.1 Statutory and Regulatory Basis\n\nIn accordance with Paragraph 3.5 of the 2026 FIU-IND Guidelines, the Company has adopted a Board-approved Client Acceptance Framework for the purpose of identifying the types of clients that are likely to pose a higher ML/TF/PF risk.\n\n### 7.2 Core Principles of Client Acceptance\n\nIn accordance with Paragraph 3.5 of the 2026 Guidelines, the Client Acceptance Framework of the Company is built on the following principles:\n\n(a) **No relationship without CDD (Paragraph 3.5(a)):** No relationship or transaction shall be initiated without implementing the appropriate Client Due Diligence (CDD) measures as set out in Section 10 of this Policy;\n\n(b) **Prohibition on anonymous or fictitious accounts (Paragraph 3.5(b)):** The Company shall not allow the opening of, or keep, any anonymous account, account in fictitious names, or accounts on behalf of other persons whose identity has not been disclosed or cannot be verified;\n\n(c) **Triggering enhanced measures on discrepancy (Paragraph 3.5(c)):** Any discrepancy, mismatch, or non-verification of information shall result in the triggering of enhanced measures under CDD, as applicable, in accordance with Section 11 of this Policy;\n\n(d) **Termination on CDD failure (Paragraph 3.5(d)):** In cases where the Company is not able to ascertain the identity of the client, or the information provided by the client is suspected to be false or non-genuine, or appropriate CDD measures or enhanced measures under CDD cannot be applied, the onboarding process shall be terminated and no transaction shall be allowed for such client;\n\n(e) **Sanctions list screening at onboarding (Paragraph 3.5(e)):** A system shall be implemented to ensure that the identity of the client does not match with any person or entity appearing in the Sanctions Lists. Detailed sanctions screening requirements are set out in Section 14 of this Policy;\n\n(f) **Closure of existing accounts without records (Paragraph 3.5(f)):** In case the Company does not have records of the identity of any existing clients (as prescribed under Chapter 4 of the 2026 Guidelines and Section 10 of this Policy), the Company shall obtain such records in a time-bound manner, failing which the Company shall close the account of such clients after giving due notice."
