      "text": "\n### 7.3 Categories of Clients Not Onboarded\n\nIn alignment with the Client Acceptance Framework principles set out in Section 7.2 and the Risk Assessment framework set out in Section 8 of this Policy, the Company shall not onboard the following categories of prospective clients:\n\n(a) Any person or entity whose identity matches with any person or entity appearing in the Sanctions Lists (UNSCR designations, UAPA designations, WMDA-related designations) at the time of onboarding;\n\n(b) Persons who refuse or are unable to provide identification documents or information required under CDD as set out in Section 10 of this Policy;\n\n(c) Persons in respect of whom enhanced measures under CDD cannot be applied where such measures are mandatorily required under Paragraph 4.4 of the 2026 Guidelines and Section 11 of this Policy;\n\n(d) Persons whose identity, source of funds, or beneficial ownership cannot be ascertained to the satisfaction of the Company;\n\n(e) Anonymous accounts and accounts in fictitious names;\n\n(f) Accounts opened on behalf of unidentified persons."
