      "text": "\n\n### 7.4 Operational Disclosure Regarding Banking Integration Status\n\nThe Company recognises that, given its current pre-banking or unbanked operational status, certain client-facing communications and onboarding flows must address banking integration arrangements transparently. Specifically:\n\n(a) Client-facing onboarding materials shall clearly describe the Company's current arrangements for fiat-to-VDA and VDA-to-fiat settlement, including any third-party payment service provider relationships used;\n\n(b) Where customer funds may be processed through accounts not directly controlled by the Company, the Company shall maintain documented arrangements with such third parties addressing AML/CFT/CPF allocation of responsibilities;\n\n(c) The Company shall not represent to customers that funds are held in any banking arrangement that does not exist;\n\n(d) The Company shall not facilitate any onboarding or transaction where the absence of stable banking integration would result in inability to maintain Travel Rule data, transaction records, or sanctions screening clearance to standards required by this Policy;\n\n(e) The Principal Officer shall maintain a continuous assessment of how the Company's banking integration status affects ML/TF/PF risk and shall reassess this evaluation periodically (at minimum semi-annually) and upon material changes.\n\nThis operational consideration is not a regulatory requirement under the 2026 Guidelines but reflects the Company's commitment to operational transparency and risk management."
