      "text": "\n\n### 7.6 Retail Onboarding Specifics\n\nGiven the Company's retail customer base, retail onboarding shall implement the following specific operational requirements:\n\n(a) **Liveness verification:** Every retail onboarding shall include liveness detection technology to confirm the physical presence of the individual, in accordance with Paragraph 4.2.4 of the 2026 Guidelines;\n\n(b) **Geo-location capture:** Retail onboarding shall capture geo-coordinates (latitude/longitude) with timestamp and IP address, in accordance with Paragraph 4.2.5 of the 2026 Guidelines;\n\n(c) **Penny-drop bank verification:** Bank account ownership and operational status shall be verified through a penny-drop mechanism, in accordance with Paragraph 4.2.6 of the 2026 Guidelines;\n\n(d) **PAN mandatory:** PAN verification is mandatory for every retail onboarding;\n\n(e) **Identity document:** One of the prescribed documents (Passport, Driving Licence, Aadhaar proof, or Voter's ID) is mandatory.\n\nDetailed CDD requirements for individuals are set out in Section 10 of this Policy."
